Homepage at Northwestern University Libraries Digital Collections

The Northwestern University Photographs Collection was created by University Archives staff from a variety of sources, and originally served as an internal reference collection. Organized by topic, the photographs found here document people, events, buildings, and activities at Northwestern University from the institution's founding up through present day. Formats found here are primarily photographic prints, but also include some negatives, transparencies, and earlier formats such as daguerreotypes.
